28. Find the Index of the First Occurrence in a String
Problem

Given two strings:

haystack (text)
needle (pattern)

Return the index of the first occurrence of needle in haystack.

If needle is not present, return -1.

Example 1
Input:
haystack = "sadbutsad"
needle = "sad"

Output:
0
Example 2
Input:
haystack = "leetcode"
needle = "leeto"

Output:
-1
Key Observation

We need to find the first occurrence of one string inside another.

Possible approaches:

Brute Force
Using substring()
Rabin-Karp (Rolling Hash)
KMP (Most Optimal)

Approach 1: Brute Force (Naive String Matching)
Intuition

Check every possible starting index in haystack.

Compare characters one by one.

If all characters match, return the starting index.

Java
class Solution {

    public int strStr(String haystack, String needle) {

        int n = haystack.length();
        int m = needle.length();

        if (m == 0) return 0;

        for (int i = 0; i <= n - m; i++) {

            int j = 0;

            while (j < m && haystack.charAt(i + j) == needle.charAt(j)) {
                j++;
            }

            if (j == m)
                return i;
        }

        return -1;
    }
}
