Approach 2: Using substring()
Intuition

Extract every substring of length needle.length() and compare it with needle.

Java
class Solution {

    public int strStr(String haystack, String needle) {

        int n = haystack.length();
        int m = needle.length();

        if (m == 0) return 0;

        for (int i = 0; i <= n - m; i++) {

            if (haystack.substring(i, i + m).equals(needle))
                return i;
        }

        return -1;
    }
}
Complexity
Time: O(nm)
Space: O(m)

Approach 3: Rabin-Karp (Rolling Hash)
Intuition

Instead of comparing every character,

compare the hash of the pattern with the hash of the current window.

If hashes match,

verify the substring to avoid collisions.

Rolling Hash

Instead of recomputing the hash every time,

Old Window

↓

Remove Left Character

↓

Multiply Remaining Hash

↓

Add New Character

↓

New Window Hash
Java (Your Code)
class Solution {

    public int strStr(String haystack, String needle) {

        if (needle.length() > haystack.length()) {
            return -1;
        }

        if (needle.length() == 0) {
            return 0;
        }

        int prime = 256;
        int base = 101;

        int m = needle.length();
        int n = haystack.length();

        int patternHash = 0;
        int windowHash = 0;

        int h = 1;

        for (int i = 0; i < m - 1; i++) {
            h = (h * base) % prime;
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
            patternHash = (base * patternHash + needle.charAt(i)) % prime;
            windowHash = (base * windowHash + haystack.charAt(i)) % prime;
        }

        for (int i = 0; i <= n - m; i++) {

            if (patternHash == windowHash) {

                if (haystack.substring(i, i + m).equals(needle))
                    return i;
            }

            if (i < n - m) {

                windowHash =
                        (base * (windowHash - haystack.charAt(i) * h)
                                + haystack.charAt(i + m)) % prime;

                if (windowHash < 0)
                    windowHash += prime;
            }
        }

        return -1;
    }
}
